<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Afghanistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hekmatyar Offensive Said `Repulsed' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hekmatyar Offensive Said `Repulsed' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0404210694 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 4 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0404210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The offensive of Golboddin Hekmatyar's militia in 
Tagab was repulsed. A source in the Ministry of Defense told 
the BIA military correspondent that yesterday Golboddin 
Hekmatyar's militia mounted a sudden offensive on the front 
lines of the front and high points. As a result of the kindness 
of the great God and the valor of the mojahedin of Islam it was 
dislodged. As a result of the counteroffensive of the mojahedin 
of the Islamic army, eight raiders were killed, three were taken 
prisoner, and three others were wounded. Three rocket 
launchers, three PK machine guns, and 13 Kalashnikovs were 
captured from the enemy. According to the security sources' 
report, the Tagab offensive took place as a result of Dostam's 
request that Hekmatyar open a second front against the forces of 
the Islamic army to [words indistinct] on central bases of the 
militia in the north. 

</TEXT>

